The paper uses Kolmogorov complexity theory to define and analyze the concept of facticity in data sets, which is closely related to information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the tension between structural and ad-hoc information in data sets, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the facticity threshold and the sawtooth curves observed in complex systems, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the objective measurement of tension in data sets, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
